    A name for an item of market data.

    The name is used to locate an item in market data. While a MarketDataId is unique within a system, a MarketDataName is not. However, it is intended to be unique within any single coherent data set.

    For example, a curve group contains a set of curves, and within the group the name is unique. But the market data system may contain many curve groups where the same name appears in each group. The MarketDataId includes both the group name and curve name in order to ensure uniqueness.
